  "text": "Web services provide higher abstractions and enable \"componentizing\" service functions. Hence, enterprises are able to effectively automate their business processes producing results in an unprecedented speed [CITATION_1] . However, service activities are still prone to intentional and unintentional errors because of the intensive interactions between people and machines. Ramamoorthy describes the layered hierarchical model ( Table 1) as an effective approach for reducing errors in service functions. He recommends that by enhancing users' convenience, enterprises can reduce the incidence of errors, and thereby improve their productivity and quality of work. Personalization enhancements are not comprehensive in service software and enterprises must improve them for reducing service errors. ",
